**Naval Reactors Interview Travel Program funding supports Navy Nuclear submarine enlisted to travel for conducting interviews with the Director of Naval Reactors and every
Nuclear sailor prior to initiating training at Nuclear Power Training University (NPTU) Charleston, NPTU Ballston Spa (B/S) and Navy Nuclear Power Training Command
(NNPTC).
**White Hat Training Facility funds provide equipment and install of fuel, Sliding Padeye, and Slewing Arm Davit (SLAD) miniature crane task trainers in order to maintain
training while the White Hat training facility is under renovations. Funding also supports contractor operation and maintenance of simulators (COMS).
* Funding for this program is realigned to from BA 1, Combat Support Forces (1C6C) in FY 2026.
**Programs funds exist in year of execution, FY 2024 only.

II. Force Structure Summary:
     Specialized Skill Training is comprised of approximately 2,600 courses with an average workload of approximately 23,682 students. Temporary Duty Under
     Instruction (TEMDUINS), Surface Warfare Officer's Division Officer Course (SWOSDOC) and Directed Training provide approximately 25,117 officers and
     enlisted training opportunities each year.

    This Sub-Activity Group also provides support for Ready Relevant Learning (RRL). In FY 2026, RRL will make significant progress towards program
    milestones across all three Lines of Effort (LOE) (1-Career-Long Learning Continuums (CLLC), 2-Modern Delivery at Point of Need, and 3-Integrated Content
    Development).

    Learning Centers
        Center for Explosive Ordnance Disposal and Diving (CEODD)
        Center for Information Warfare Training (CIWT)
        Center for Naval Aviation Technical Training (CNATT)
        Center for Seabees and Facilities Engineering (CSFE)
