      i)Navy College Program for Afloat College Education (NPACE): Resources decrease to eliminate NCPACE, a critical                     -1,157
         educational program designed for Sailors operating in environments with limited communication access, including those
         aboard submarines, deployed ships, and in remote or forward-deployed locations (Type II and IV duty). (Baseline: $1,133)
      ii)Voluntary Business Operations. Resources decrease to eliminate 12 civilian FTEs and support for Voluntary Business               -1,348
         Operations, which manage accounting support for various programs, including the Navy College Management Information
         System (NCMIS) database. The NCMIS is instrumental in processing education vouchers for Navy programs such as STA-
         21, AEV/GEV, and JST, and importantly, extends Tuition Assistance services to both the Marine Corps and Coast Guard.
         (Baseline: $1,320; -12 civilian FTE)
      iii)Virtual Education Center: Resources decrease to eliminate 55 civilian FTEs and support for the Navy Voluntary Education         -8,118
         Program (VOLED) and USMAP. The elimination of VOLED will severely impact over 330,000 Sailors by limiting their
         ability to pursue higher education and earn certifications-opportunities essential for enhancing Navy competitiveness and
         facilitating successful transitions to civilian life. (Baseline: $7,951; -55 civilian FTE)
      iv)Tuition Assistance (TA): Decrease in funding to align with the Secretary of Defense's priorities to rebuild the military,       -37,885
         reinforce the warrior ethos, and enhance deterrence, funding for active-duty TA is eliminated within the Discretionary
         Budget, significantly reducing education and career advancement opportunities for active-duty service members.
         Additionally, the Selected Reserve (SELRES) TA program will experience a substantial funding reduction, limiting
         educational access for reservists and potentially affecting their professional development and retention. (Baseline: $62,083)
