        630                                                                                                                                                       (Page 4 of 16)
                                                                            Department of the Navy
                                                                   FY 2026 President's Budget Submission
                                                                       Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                          Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                                     Activity Group: Servicewide Support
                                                      Detail by Subactivity Group: Military Manpower and Personnel Mgt
ADE will need to interface and integrate with all MyNavy HR transactional and business systems, including enabling 'plug & play' of new services, technologies, and system
capabilities.

Enterprise Customer Relationship Management (eCRM): The Enterprise Customer Relationship Management (eCRM) is a software solution that will integrate business
processes, supporting systems, and authoritative data in support of Navy Personnel Command's (NPC's) MNCC (My Navy Career Center), Navy Recruiting Command (NRC),
Navy Education & Training Command (NETC), and other commands that manage the Navy workforce. The eCRM solution provides an approach to manage information on
current and future Sailors, veterans, and their families. The following segments organize the eCRM solution: 1) Sales Management, 2) Knowledge Management, 3) Case
Management, 4) Performance Management, and 5) Recruiting

Legacy Manpower Systems: Legacy Manpower Systems is a portfolio of Human Resource IT Business Systems that support active, reserve and retired personnel. This Portfolio
includes the following systems: Medical Readiness Reporting System (MRRS), Total Force Manpower Management System (TFMMS), Departmental (DEPT), Officer Promotion
Administrative System (OPAS), Enlisted Assignment Information System (EAIS), Officer Assignment Information System (OAIS), and MyNavy Assignment (MNA)

Navy Standard Integrated Personnel System (NSIPS): The Navy Standard Integrated Personnel System (NSIPS) is the Navy's business solution to Human Resource
Management for approximately 400,000 sailors worldwide. It serves as the Navy's single, field-entry, electronic pay and personnel system for all active-duty and reserve Sailors
and is available world-wide, ashore and afloat.

MyNavy HR IT Solutions: MyNavy HR IT Solutions Program Management Office (PMO), which falls under PEO Manpower, Logistics, and Business Solutions (MLB), is
responsible for the operation and maintenance of approximately 70 MyNavy HR applications. The Sea Warrior Program Office provides acquisition and program management for
MyNavy HR information technology (IT) program.

Joint Air Logistic Information System (JALIS): Air logistics depend on JALIS. JALIS is a multipurpose on-demand automated scheduling program for operational scheduling,
aircraft management, and data analysis that allows DoD service personnel to submit airlift requirements for DoD personnel and cargo, air logistics flying units to communicate
their aircraft availability in a real-time graphic display, and designated scheduling organizations to compare airlift requirements to available aircraft and create mission
assignments. JALIS alerts users on mission information and changes via system displays and email. The geographically distributed JALIS scheduling capability moves thousands
of DoD personnel and tons of cargo annually in support of Navy Unique Fleet Essential Airlift, Army's Operational Support Airlift Agency (OSAA), US Transportation Command
(USTRANSCOM), and USMC.




