                                                        Detail by Subactivity Group: Military Manpower and Personnel Mgt
II. Force Structure Summary:

The Bureau of Naval Personnel (BUPERS) provides support for officer and enlisted personnel distribution, career development, personnel administration, and other functions
supporting the Chief of Naval Personnel (CHNAVPERS). BUPERS functions include: a) operating automated military manpower and personnel management information systems;
b) controlling, maintaining, updating, and administering personnel records for all current and former members of the Navy and Navy Reserve; c) tracking individuals on appellate
leave, and d) reducing the cost of entitlements for medical and other benefits. Also, BUPERS personnel perform budgeting and accounting services for the Military Personnel,
Navy (MPN) Appropriation and the Full Time Support (FTS) portion of the Reserve Personnel, Navy (RPN) Appropriation. This program also manages and administers the
centralized cost accounting, reporting and statistical systems for obligating, reporting, and controlling funds appropriated for costs associated with the Consecutive Overseas Tours
Program; produces reports and other statistical data; reviews voucher payments; adjusts charges against the Training and Administration of the Naval Reserve Appropriation, and
manages the Permanent Change of Station Travel Advance Liquidation System.

The Navy Personnel Command (NPC) performs the human resource function for all US Navy personnel. Functions include establishing policies and procedures, maintaining
processing systems, and providing document processing support for all US Navy commands and personnel from enlistment to retirement to include Permanent Change of Station
and Temporary Duty Instruction. NPC provides payroll support for the US Navy through its Personnel Support Detachments located worldwide. This command also serves as the
repository for Official Military Records. Those records are used throughout a Sailor's career to determine eligibility for continued service, reenlistment options, and selection for
promotion. NPC's mission is to provide the Fleet with the right person in the right place at the right time. Programs within this budget activity support the entire Navy.




