         the Quality-of-Service for Sailors in high suicide risk areas. These programs aim to reduce stress and harmful behaviors,
         while improving Sailor resilience and stress management through subclinical interventions and access to licensed clinicians
         as recommended by the USS George Washington Phase II investigation. (Baseline: $35,942)
      vii)My Navy Career Center (MNCC)/Personnel Administrative Support System (PASS): Resources increased due to a                            3,294
         realignment to provide for contractor labor for the Personnel Service Centers who provide Tier 1 pay and personnel support
         to more than 300,000 sailors through all career and life events. (Baseline: $153,651)
      viii)SAPR-IRC: Resources increased for travel and contracts to ensure implementation of the Independent Review                           2,477
         Commission's recommendations to prevent sexual assault in the military as mandated by the Secretary of Defense. (Baseline:
         $5,181)
