NAVAIR maintains and prepares the upkeep of force protection and self-defense of its operational capabilities against Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS) threats. Requirement
drivers are based on Congressional direction, SECDEF and Service policy and guidance, as well as technical sustainment requirements of the Physical Security Programs. Funding
is provided to protect high value/critical Navy assets, and support public safety against threats from inadvertent or unlawful misuse of UAS. This funding is used for procurement,
fielding, sustainment, and training of Counter-Unmanned Aerial systems (C-UAS) for Navy C-UAS and C-UxS programs under the Physical Security Program umbrella.


