        693                                                                                                                                                       (Page 1 of 15)
                                                                     Department of the Navy
                                                             FY 2026 President's Budget Submission
                                                               Operation and Maintenance, Navy
                                                   Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                  Activity Group: Logistics Operations And Technical Support
                                                Detail by Subactivity Group: Acquisition, Logistics, and Oversight

Contracting Services: Serves as Navy's Lead Contracting Executive (LCE) for contracting support for logistics, ship port visits, regional contracts serving multiple
commands, business and support services to fleet, shore and industrial commands, and other allied forces. The FLCs are responsible for Global Husbanding Service
Provider (HSP) services for naval vessels and units deployed worldwide.

Bulk Petroleum Support/Fuel Services: delivers bulk and retail petroleum services to the Fleet and other Department of Defense (DoD) and non-DoD customers
worldwide. These services operate petroleum, oil, and lubricants systems at bulk and aviation fuel terminals, determining and fulfilling both peacetime and wartime
requirements, by providing inventory management, financial accountability, and quality assurance and testing on all delivered products. They also maintain, repair, and
upgrade fuel facilities as required to ensure safe, continued operations for current and future requirements.

Global Logistics: Directly supports Navy fleet and operational readiness by providing an integrated 24/7 "front door" for Navy and joint service forces to communicate
material and other logistics support requirements to ashore providers. Program employs information technology, telephonic, and face to face interface to deliver timely
and authoritative logistics expertise to assist fleet customers on a full spectrum of supply and logistic issues. Program satisfies fleet support requests by either direct
action or by passing the requirement to appropriate logistics agency.

Provides supply department ashore for the Littoral Combat Ships (LCS). Due to their reduced manning levels, LCS requires NAVSUP to perform supply functions such
as planning, supply records keeping, commodity forecasting and a full range of logistics coordination supporting LCS platforms operating worldwide.

The Global Fleet Logistics Centers complete an average of 190K logistics actions requested by over 8,000 unique customers from Navy ships, aircraft squadrons, units,
Joint and Allied Department of Defense activities.

Ammunition Supply Chain Management: Navy's provider of conventional ordnance inventory and logistics for the Navy/Marine Corps. Global presence of ordnance
logistics experts provide front-line customer support and training to the warfighter. Develop, implement, and administer Naval ordnance stockpile management policies
and procedures.

Ordnance Information Systems (OIS): Program management of web-based ordnance logistics and inventory management tools. OIS is the Department of the Navy's
Accountable Property System of Record supporting Navy, USMC aviation, and USCG. NAVSUP is the single point of reference for information/processes regarding the
over 180 end-to-end logistics processes within the ammunition supply chain.


Navy Charge Cards/Defense Travel System

Department of Navy (DON) Government Purchase Card (GPC) Program, Navy Government Travel Charge Card (GTCC), DON Government Fuel Card (GFC) programs
and the Navy Defense Travel System (DTS) Management Program.

Department of the Navy (DON) financial charge card programs include: the DON Government Purchase Card (GPC), the Navy Government Travel Charge Card (GTCC)
program, and the DON Fuel Card programs (Fleet, Aviation Into-plane Reimbursement (AIR) Card ®, Ships' bunkers' Easy Acquisition (SEA) Card®, and the Swipe
SEA Card®). Also included is the Navy Defense Travel System (DTS) program management office. These programs are within the NAVSUP DON Consolidated Card
Program management Division (CCPMD) centrally located and consolidated within the Naval Supply System Command, Corporate Operations Directorate. The DON
                                                                                                                                           $$, $$bb92760656eb2607155579b9cb0b0c97a862eb1f4bf8d8380b2d1ecefe8b40c4$$, $$O&M/FY26/Navy/OMN_Book.pdf$$, NULL, $$2026-05-07T23:02:19.21198+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
