                                                           Budget Activity: Administration and Servicewide Activities
                                                          Activity Group: Logistics Operations And Technical Support
                                                        Detail by Subactivity Group: Acquisition, Logistics, and Oversight

II. Force Structure Summary:
This sub-activity group provides for the acquisition, program management, logistic operations and support of various programs. Specific organizations that are funded include:

Naval Supply Systems Command (NAVSUP) – This sub-activity group provides for the operations and support of various logistical and technical programs. Specific
organizations that are funded include the Navy Exchange Service Command (NEXCOM), NAVSUP Weapons Systems Support Transportation & Distribution (NAVSUP WSS
T&D), NAVSUP's eight Fleet Logistics Centers (NAVSUP FLCs), and program management at NAVSUP Headquarters.

Naval Air Systems Command (NAVAIR) – This sub-activity group supports approximately 1,221, civilians and 79 military personnel who manage and support 510 aviation and
47 Command and Administration programs/projects totaling 557 that are managed by NAVAIR headquarters, Patuxent River, MD. It also provides managerial oversight to civilian
and military personnel of the Naval Aviation Systems Team located in the Patuxent River, MD area headquarters to include five (5) Program Executive Officers (PEOs) and four
(4) Expense Operating Budget (EOB) activities, two (2) Naval Aviation Warfare Centers (NAWC) and three (3) Fleet Readiness Centers (FRC).

Department of the Navy (DON) – This sub-activity group provides for the operation or support of various logistic and technical programs. Specific organizations that are funded
include the Assistant Secretary of the Navy (Research, Development, and Acquisition) (ASN-RD&A)), the International Programs Office (Navy-IPO), and the Naval Acquisition
Career Center (NACC).




