        (Baseline: $369,621)
      vii) Efficiency – Travel: Reduce discretionary travel funding to align with Executive Order 14222, Implementing the                   -2,948
        President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative. (Baseline: $555,916)
      viii) Personnel Security Investigations (PSI) - Decrease in support funding for initial background investigations, adjudications,      -5,822
        Continues Vetting (CV) enrollments, fingerprints and periodic reinvestigations. The DON is covering the subscription for the
        entire Navy and Marine Corps population, which accounts for over one million enrollees. (Baseline: $255,656)
      ix) Sexual Assault Prevention and Response - Decrease in support funding due to reduced requirements for investigative               -11,028
        sexual harassment efforts, to include travel, training, vehicles, IT and forensic equipment, user software licenses, SharePoint/
        cloud migrations. (Baseline: $81,896)
      x) Efficiency – Contract Services: Reduces contracts for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and                 -14,891
        advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, Implementing the President's
        Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative. (Baseline: $976,135)
      xi) Efficiency – Workforce Optimization: Reduces civilian personnel full-time equivalent and associated funding in                    -21,805
        accordance with Executive Order 14210, Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce
        Optimization Initiative. (Baseline: $122,780; -105 civilian FTE)




